The Observability Infrastructure Team is responsible for (1) an in-house developed time-series database, time-series warehouse, distributed tracing, and logging systems (2) a one-stop observability platform including application monitoring, customized dashboard, intelligent alarm, problem diagnosis, and remediation, tracing topology analysis, in order to guarantee production service stability, capacity management, and service governance capabilities.

What you will be doing:
1. Create a one-stop Observability Platform that includes capabilities such as application monitoring, distribution tracing, diagnosis workflow, and self-service repair platform;
2. Responsible for promoting the implementation of business indicators and call link management specifications;
3. Improve troubleshooting efficiency and automation efficiency. 

Qualifications

 What you should have:
1. Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or related fields with at least 4 years of experience;
2. Proficient in Golang (GO) programming language and familiar with common Linux commands;
3. Experience in customization development and deep knowledge of open-source monitoring ecosystems (OpenTracing, Prometheus, falcon, etc.)
4. Familiar with MySQL or any relational database, with certain SQL writing skills and optimization experience;
5. Work conscientiously and steadfastly, with strong learning ability and problem-solving abilities;
6. Strong product awareness, good at getting close to users, refining user pain points, and creating a closed loop of product experience.

